Persian Gulf Stocks: Aldar Properties, Arabtec Holding Decline

-- B y   Z a h r a   H a n k i r
-- 
2011-08-07T14:10:12Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-07/persian-gulf-stocks-aldar-properties-arabtec-holding-decline.html
Dubai’s  DFM General Index (DFMGI)  tumbled 3.7
percent, the most since Feb. 28, to 1,484.31 at the 2:00 p.m. in
the emirate.  Abu Dhabi ’s  ADX General Index (ADSMI)  fell 2.5 percent.  The following shares were active in the Persian Gulf
region. Stock symbols are in parenthesis.        Aldar Properties PJSC (ALDAR)   tumbled 6.3 percent to
1.20 dirhams, the lowest on record. Abu Dhabi’s biggest real-
estate company reported a second-quarter profit of 127.3 million
dirhams ($34.7 million), missing analysts’ estimates for a
profit of 153 million dirhams.        Arabtec Holding Co. (ARTC)   retreated 6.3 percent, the
most since March 2, to 1.34 dirhams. The United Arab Emirates’
biggest construction company by market value said second-quarter
profit dropped 74 percent to 28.97 million dirhams. The mean
estimate of six analysts was for a profit of 44 million dirhams.  Saudi Arabian Refinery Co. (SARCO AB) declined 3.1 percent
to 40.30 riyals, the lowest level since May 2. The company
investing in oil refineries and fuel distribution said its
lawsuit against Abdullah & Saeed Bin Zaqer Co. will resume on
Oct. 25.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Zahra Hankir in Dubai at 
 zhankir@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
